  "prompt": "Can I use my VSP insurance to purchase glasses at LensCrafters?",
  "response": "Yes, you can typically use your VSP (Vision Service Plan) insurance to purchase glasses at LensCrafters. VSP is a vision insurance provider that partners with various retailers, including LensCrafters, to offer coverage for vision-related services and products, including frames and lenses. However, it's a good idea to confirm specific benefits, coverage limits, and any necessary steps with both VSP and LensCrafters before making a purchase. You can also check if the LensCrafters location near you is in-network with VSP to maximize your benefits.",
